Dependencies:
    Python 2.6:
    (either run as root or inside a virtualenv)
    fabric 0.9.2+:

    RabbitMQ (maybe)

System prerequisites:
1. python 2.6+ with easy_install
2. sqlite3 for dev database
3. mercurial

Steps to install:
1. download and install easy_install
2. sudo easy_install pip
3. sudo pip install virtualenv (if you don't want to muck up your base python system)
4. sudo pip install fabric
5. fab setup - this creates a virtualenv in ~/.virtualenvs/vcweb by default
6. add an alias to your .bashrc:
alias vcweb='. ~/.virtualenvs/vcweb/bin/activate'
this activates your virtualenv
7. fab syncdb
8. fab server (in one terminal)
9. fab tornadio (in another terminal) if you want to run vcweb w/ server push enabled.

To start up celeryd and celerybeat

./manage.py celeryd
./manage.py celerybeat

(or fab celeryd / celerybeat)
